Isle of Faces06978mw54ij1jtmokhd5yz7btocgzpovygsa1603992014-09-24T19:34:06ZThe Dragon Demands5014364[[File:IsleOfFaces.png|thumb|300px|Faces were carved into every tree on the island]]
{{Quote|To seal the Pact before the gods, the Children carved a face on every weirwood tree on the island, which came to be known as the Isle of Faces.|[[Bran Stark]]|The Children of the Forest, the First Men, and the Andals}}
The '''Isle of Faces''' is an island located at the center of [[Gods Eye]], an immense lake on the south-eastern edge of the [[Riverlands]] and the north-western edge of the [[Crownlands]]. The castle of [[Harrenhal]] lies on the coast of the lake to the north of the island.&lt;ref&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season1/#!/locations/twins/ HBO viewers guide, season 1 map, The Twins entry]&lt;/ref&gt;&lt;ref&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/game-of-thrones/season2/#!/locations/harrenhall/ HBO viewers guide, season 2 map, Harrenhal entry]&lt;/ref&gt;
